EMPANGENI, KZN - Restoring unity within the A-N-C tops the party s to-do list in KwaZulu-Natal.The Provincial General Council began at the University of Zululand on Friday.It was opened by President Jacob Zuma and attended by several members of the National Executive Committee.The province is well-aware of the power it wields in determining the party s future.At the Provincial General Council, its key focus is getting all branches to speak in one voice.And speakers repeatedly drove this point home.READ: ANC in KZN to march over 'judicial overreach'Click on the below video for the full report. eNCA